============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Dialectical Materialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   History driven by material economic forces through thesis-antithesis-synthesis
Philosopher:  Karl Marx/Hegel
Example:      Class struggle between bourgeoisie and proletariat drives history

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Market Failure
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Free markets fail to allocate resources efficiently
Formula:    Social cost = private + external cost
Economist:  Arthur Pigou
Example:    Carbon emissions: negative externality requiring government intervention

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

Concept:    Keynesian Economics
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government fiscal policy stabilizes economy in recessions
Formula:    AD = C + I + G + NX
Economist:  John Maynard Keynes
Example:    2009 US stimulus; 2020-2021 COVID relief spending

